'''Берн''' ({{lang-de|Bern}}, {{lang-fr|Berne}}) — двуязычный кантон на западе центральной части [[Швейцария|Швейцарии]]. Административный центр — город [[Берн]]. Население 992 617 человека (2-е место среди кантонов; данные [[2012 год]]а).

== География ==
<!--
[[Файл:Erlenbach Simmental.jpg|thumb|left|150px|The Simmental]][[Файл:Unterer Engstligenfall4.jpg|thumb|left|150px|A Waterfall in the Eastern Oberland]][[Файл:Mönch.jpg|thumb|150px|left|The [[Mönch]](13’474 ft) covered in ice and glaciers]]

The '''canton of Berne''' is the second largest of all Swiss cantons. It borders the [[кантон Юра]] and the [[кантон Золотурн]] to the north. To the west lie the [[кантон Невшатель]], the [[кантон Фрибур]] and [[Во]], to the south lies the [[Вале]]. East of the canton of Berne lie the cantons of [[кантон Ури|Ури]], [[Нидвальден]], [[Обвальден]], [[кантон Люцерн|Люцерн]] and [[Ааргау]].

The canton of Berne is mainly drained by the River [[Аара]] and its tributaries. The area of the canton is commonly divided into three areas. The [[Bernese Oberland]] (''Berner Oberland'') lies in the south of the canton and is part of the [[Альпы]]. The highest elevation in the Bernese Oberland is the [[Финстерархорн]] (4 274 м). The famous hiking and ski resorts in the eastern oberland around [[Интерлакен]] and the [[Юнгфрау]] (4 158 м) are located within this area, such as car free [[Wengen]] & [[Mürren]] and [[Gimmelwald]] & [[Гриндельвальд]], with further east the [[Aareschlucht]] and the town of [[Meiringen]] famous for a fateful scene of [[Шерлок Холмс]]'s death on a high waterfall. There are many other resorts and small villages catering to visitors who prefer even greater isolation and the western oberland is less known. In the Western Bernese Oberland accessed from the large scenic lake town of [[Thun]] the most notable are [[Kandersteg]] & the [[OeschinenSee]], as well as [[Kiental]] and [[Adelboden]]. Going further west up the even more secluded [[Simmental]] river valleys one reaches [[Zweisimmen]], [[Lenk]], [[Gstaad]], and [[Saanen]].

[[Файл:Lüderenalp.jpg|thumb|right|225px|The Napf region above the Emme river]][[Файл:Bielersee.jpg|thumb|225px|right|[[Бильское озеро]]]]
The whole area in the south is very mountainous, with steep cliffs, many glaciers, and countless waterfalls, and renowned thruout the world for its scenic beauty and the charm of the small swiss villages that dot the area. As a result of this [[tourism]] is one of the main sources of income in the Bernese Oberland and even when going over a remote pass one finds often a small farmhouse on the way up or a mountain cabin willing to give accommodation and dinner to the passerby. Typically selling the local cheeses and specialty products with the ubiquitous spring water pouring out of the fountains and taps for the hikers to quench their thirst. The region also has an extensive train network as well as many [[aerial tramway|cable cars]], [[gondola lift|gondolas]], [[chairlift|lifts]], and [[funicular]]s, with the highest train station in Europe, the longest funicular in Europe, and the longest gondola cableway in the world.
-->
